Tobishima rises after creditors OK restructuring . Tobishima Corp shares rose early on Tuesday morning after Monday ' s news that its creditors had formally agreed to a restructuring plan that would reduce its group debt to 100 billion yen , brokers said . As of 0042 GMT , shares in the debt - burdened construction firm were up six yen at 210 . The restructuring was in line with a basic agreement Tobishima reached with its creditors in March , which included a reduction in creditors ' claims against the builder to 100 billion yen from 740 billion yen . 
